---
import NoteBox from "@components/NoteBox.astro";
import Layout from "@layouts/Layout.astro";
import PageHeroVisual from "@components/PageHeroVisual.astro";
import LabNoteFooter from "@components/LabNoteFooter.astro";
import { PERSON, SITE } from "@data/site";

const title = "Why Many LMD RFQs Fail Before Engineering Review";
const description =
  "Many Laser Metal Deposition RFQs fail early because they omit material, damage, access, tolerance, inspection, and operating-condition context.";
const jsonLd = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "Article",
  headline: title,
  description,
  author: { "@id": `${SITE.canonicalUrl}/identity#manish-sharma`, name: PERSON.name },
  datePublished: SITE.lastUpdated,
  dateModified: SITE.lastUpdated,
  url: `${SITE.canonicalUrl}/lab-notes/why-many-lmd-rfqs-fail-before-engineering-review`
};
---

<Layout title={`${title} — Manish Sharma Lab`} description={description} canonical="/lab-notes/why-many-lmd-rfqs-fail-before-engineering-review" jsonLd={jsonLd}>
  <article class="site-shell py-16 md:py-20">
    <div class="grid gap-10 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_minmax(24rem,0.62fr)] lg:items-center">
      <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="metric-label">Lab note · 2026-05-09</p>
      <h1 class="mt-5 text-5xl font-black leading-tight text-white md:text-6xl">{title}</h1>
      </div>
      <PageHeroVisual variant="tools" class="hidden lg:block" />
    </div>
    <div class="mt-10 grid gap-6 lg:grid-cols-[0.75fr_1.25fr]">
      <div class="grid h-fit gap-4">
        <NoteBox title="Short answer">
          Weak RFQs fail because the decision-critical information is missing before anyone can responsibly discuss feasibility.
        </NoteBox>
        <NoteBox title="Common mistake" tone="laser">
          Asking “can this be repaired by LMD?” without material grade, damage depth, access, tolerance, inspection requirement, or operating conditions.
        </NoteBox>
        <NoteBox title="Practical takeaway" tone="steel">
          A good AI-assisted RFQ should make missing information visible instead of hiding uncertainty behind a confident recommendation.
        </NoteBox>
      </div>
      <div class="prose-lab">
        <p>
          Many Laser Metal Deposition RFQs fail before engineering review because they start with a vague part description and end with a request for a firm answer. The missing information is not administrative detail; it is the feasibility signal.
        </p>
        <p>
          The most important missing fields are often material grade, damage depth, repair-zone access, final tolerance, operating conditions, safety criticality, and inspection requirements. Without those fields, no tool should produce a firm repair recommendation.
        </p>
        <p>
          A strong RFQ separates known facts, assumptions, missing data, risk items, and next questions. That structure helps both AI agents and engineers avoid false confidence.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
    <LabNoteFooter links={[
        { label: "LMD RFQ Toolkit", href: "/agent-pack" },
        { label: "RFQ schema JSON", href: "/agent-pack/lmd-rfq-schema.json" },
        { label: "LMD Repairability Index", href: "/frameworks/lmd-repairability-index" }
      ]} />
  </article>
</Layout>
